Thanks for looking at this. Qifan made the changes for trafodion operators, I'm actually not very familiar with this code. Selva, this tool works off the EXPLAIN options 'f', so it cannot access any run-time information. Can we add the merge and UDF operators in a separate checkin, because I made a boo-boo in my local branch by doing a commit --amend, exactly what Steve said NOT to do :-( If there are other issues, we can maybe just abandon this request and I can make another one after fixing the issues.

Thanks Hans for clarification. At the run time, rowset operation is determined based on TDB attributes. So, it might be possible to massage the explain output similar to run time and then this tool can be modified. Currently, we need to decipher from the plan if it is single row get, multi-row get or scan from the full explain output. It would be good if can decipher this info easily from the explain options 'f' output and hence from this tool.
Will reopen with JIRA id.
